  "body": "**Describe the bug**\r\n\r\nIf we don't limit `maxGossipTopicConcurrency` (by default), it takes more time for a gossip to become head. If we limit it to 512, on test mainnet node it drops 35% of attestations, however the time for a block till becomes head is quite similar to stable\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1448\" alt=\"Screenshot 2023-05-01 at 13 02 39\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/10568965/235414282-c59620e4-9c2b-4f05-b208-e2a63e5ad1b1.png\">\r\n\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\n\r\nUnlimited `maxGossipTopicConcurrency` or configure it to a value that:\r\n- No dropped attestations\r\n- The time for a block to become head is the same to above\r\n",
